<br>
He shook the sandy blonde hair from his azure eyes, still so innocent looking. Upon his head was a onyx laurel crown. His body was covered by a black tunic, accented by a golden roped belt. On his sturdy shoulders rested the buckles to his knee-length cape, which was of rare snow leopard fur. He had indeed gone hunting on his little expedition. His sandels were of the usual brown leather, tied up to his ankles.<br>
<br>
